/pages/digitalModes/.title: Digital Modes
/pages/digitalModes/.body: Introduction to Digital Modes INCOMPLETE This page is incomplete, Please check back later once more content has been added. FT8 FT8 (short for Franke-Taylor design, 8-FSK modulation) is a frequency shift keying digital mode of radio communication used by amateur radio operators worldwide. Following release on June 29, 2017, by its creators Joe Taylor, K1JT, and Steve Franke, K9AN, along with the software package WSJT, FT8 was adopted rapidly, becoming the most popular digital mode recorded by automatic spotting networks such as PSK Reporter within 2 years.
